5 But while I thus in anguish lay ,
The gracious Saviour passed this way ,
The gracious Saviour passed this way , And felt His pity move ;
The sinner , by his justice slain ,
Now by His grace is born again
The sinner , by his justice slain , Now by His grace is born again And sings redeeming love .
AWAKE , my soul , in joyful lays ,
He justly claims a song from thee ;
His loving - kindness , O ! how free !

3 Though numerous hosts of mighty foes ,
Though earth and hell my way oppose ,
He safely leads my soul along ;
His loving - kindness , O ! how strong !
4 When trouble , like a gloomy cloud ,
His loving - kindness , O ! how strong ! 4 When trouble , like a gloomy cloud ,
Has gathered thick , and thundered loud ,
He near my soul has always stood ;
His loving - kindness . O ! how good !
BEHOLD a stranger at the door !
BEHOLD a stranger at the door !
He gently knocks , has knocked before ;
Has waited long - is waiting still .
You treat no other friend so ill .
